{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Grant Protected Status to UK Trig Points",
        "additional_details": "Built between 1936\u20131962, over 6,500 trig points formed the backbone of Britain\u2019s mapping system. They are historic, cultural, and landscape icons for walkers and communities. Many are now damaged or lost, with no consistent protection. Without action, we risk losing these unique markers of scientific achievement and national heritage forever.",
        "background": "Grant UK trig points protected heritage status, recognise them as nationally significant, create a national register, and ensure their preservation through listing, monitoring, and maintenance by bodies like Historic England and Ordnance Survey.",
